</exercise>
  </subsection>

  <exercises>
    <title>Exercises</title>

    <exercise><title>Fact Check - NEW INSTRUCTIONS, PLEASE CHECK</title>
  <introduction>
     <p> 
    Check to see if you remember the following facts about trigonometric graphs (or if can figure them out with out any help). Try first without looking up the information. Sketch any graphs you need on your own (without a graphing tool).
    </p>
  <aside>
    <p>
      <alert> Study tip: </alert>
    </p>
    <p>  
      These are examples of some things that you may need to use on a test or exam. You should know how to recall or find out these facts (and other similar ones) without using a textbook or calculator etc. 
    </p>
  </aside>
   </introduction>
    <webwork>
    <pg-code>
      Context("Numeric");

      $a = random(2,9,1);
      $b = random(2,9,1);
      $c = random(2,9,1);
      $ans1 = Compute("2*pi/$b")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );
      $ans2 = Compute("0")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );         
      $ans3 = Compute("1")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );
             
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
      <p> (a) Sketch a few periods of the graph of <m>y=\sin x</m>. </p>
      <p> (b) Sketch a few periods of the graph of <m>y=3\cos x</m>. </p>
      <p> (c) Sketch a few periods of the graph of <m>y=\tan (x-\pi)</m>. </p>
      <p> (d) It is true or false that <m>\tan (x-\pi) = \tan x</m>? <var name="$ans3" width="6"/> (Enter 1 for TRUE and 0 for FALSE.)  </p>                
      <p> (e) What is the period of <m>y=<var name="$a"/> \sin (<var name="$b"/> x-<var name="$c"/>)</m>? <var name="$ans1" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (f) What is <m> \tan 0</m>? <var name="$ans2" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (g) What is <m> \cos 0</m>? <var name="$ans3" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (h) What is <m> \sin (-\pi)</m>? <var name="$ans2" width="6"/></p>    
    </statement>
  </webwork>
  </exercise>

<exercise><title>Find period, amplitude, phase shift - HOMEMADE - UPDATED</title>
    <webwork>
    <pg-code>
      Context("Numeric");

      $a = random(2,9,1);
      $b = random(2,9,1);
      $c = random(2,9,1);
      $ans1 = Compute("2*pi/$b")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );
      $ans2 = Compute("$a")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );         
      $ans3 = Compute("-$c/$b")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );
      $ans4 = Compute("0")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );         
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
      <p>Find the following for the function <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x+<var name="$c"/>\right)</m></p>
      <p> (a) What is the period of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x+<var name="$c"/>\right)</m>? <var name="$ans1" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (b) What is the amplitude of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x+<var name="$c"/>\right)</m>? <var name="$ans2" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (c) What is the phase shift of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x+<var name="$c"/>\right)</m>? <var name="$ans3" width="6"/> (Use a positive number for a shift to the right, and negative for to the left.)</p>
      <p> (d) What is the midline of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x+<var name="$c"/>\right)</m>? <m>y=</m> <var name="$ans4" width="6"/></p>
    </statement>
  </webwork>
  </exercise>

  <exercise><title>Find period, amplitude, phase shift - HOMEMADE - UPDATED</title>
       <webwork>
    <pg-code>
      Context("Numeric");

      $a = random(2,9,1);
      $b = random(2,9,1);
      $c = random(2,9,1);
      $d = random(2,9,1);
      $ans1 = Compute("2*pi/$b")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );
      $ans2 = Compute("$a")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );         
      $ans3 = Compute("$c/$b")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );
      $ans4 = Compute("$d")->with(
               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );        
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
      <p>Find the following for the function <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x-<var name="$c"/>\right)+<var name="$d"/> </m></p>
      <p> (a) What is the period of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x-<var name="$c"/>\right)+<var name="$d"/> </m>? <var name="$ans1" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (b) What is the amplitude of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x-<var name="$c"/>\right)+<var name="$d"/> </m>? <var name="$ans2" width="6"/></p>
      <p> (c) What is the phase shift of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x-<var name="$c"/>\right)+<var name="$d"/> </m>? <var name="$ans3" width="6"/> (Use a positive number for a shift to the right, and negative for to the left.)</p>
      <p> (d) What is the midline of <m> y=<var name="$a"/>\sin \left(<var name="$b"/>x-<var name="$c"/>\right)+<var name="$d"/> </m>? <m>y=</m> <var name="$ans4" width="6"/></p>
    </statement>
  </webwork>
</exercise>

